com.almasb.fxgl.entity

Interface RenderLayer


  • public interface RenderLayer
    Represents a layer which is used to group objects being rendered. Layers are rendered from lower index value to higher index value. Objects with higher index value will be rendered on top of objects with lower index value.
    Author:
    Almas Baimagambetov (AlmasB) (almaslvl@gmail.com)

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      static RenderLayer BACKGROUND
      Render layer for background.

      Default render layer for entities with no specified render layer.

    • Field Detail

      • TOP

        static final RenderLayer TOP
        Default render layer for entities with no specified render layer. Note: this is the highest layer that can be used.

      • BACKGROUND

        static final RenderLayer BACKGROUND
        Render layer for background. Note: value of 1000 leaves some scope for using parallax backgrounds.
